Size: 9940
SHA256sum: 3ee6340ccf65dc525d6fe5d341a5e7b7c981ff629c6b4d2a1c2694db244751ce
Description:  This module provides support for create/encrypting/decrypting keys
 in the kernel.  Encrypted keys are kernel generated random numbers,
 which are encrypted/decrypted with a 'master' symmetric key. The
 'master' key can be either a trusted-key or user-key type.
 Userspace only ever sees/stores encrypted blobs.

Package: kmod-keys-trusted
Version: 6.6.93-r1
Depends: kernel (=6.6.93~91ddd03e06de365700718be7ef45f206-r1), kmod-crypto-hash, kmod-crypto-hmac, kmod-crypto-sha1, kmod-tpm
